messages:
Name: Gabriel Paulista
Nationality: Brazil
Date of Birth: November 26, 1990
Position: Defender
Current club: Atlético Madrid
LaLiga clubs played for: Villarreal, Valencia, Atlético Madrid

Atlético Madrid's Gabriel Paulista has made 23 appearances in this season's LaLiga, with five of these coming for his current club. He had previously played for Valencia in the competition during 2023/2024.

The last LaLiga game that Paulista played came on May 19 for Atlético Madrid versus Osasuna; a match that he played 45 minutes in during a 4-1 defeat. He has been booked five times, as well as sent off once.
In last season's Primera División, Paulista appeared in 21 games for Valencia and scored one goal.
Prior to moving to Atlético Madrid in January 2024, Paulista made 182 league appearances in total at Valencia, scoring eight goals and providing four assists.

It was on November 4, 2013 that Paulista made his LaLiga debut during his spell at Villarreal, aged 22 years and 343 days, versus Elche. He first played in a LaLiga game for current team Atlético Madrid in his team's match with Sevilla on February 11, 2024.

In his LaLiga career overall, he has appeared in 224 matches in the competition, with eight goals scored and four assists. Paulista has also been sent off five times during his LaLiga stint, with 39 yellow cards collected overall.
